==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea lion
<hw>Sea" li"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
several large species of seals of the family <fam>Otariidae</fam> native
of the Pacific Ocean, especially the southern sea lion (<spn>Otaria
jubata</spn>) of the South American coast; the northern sea lion
(<spn>Eumetopias Stelleri</spn>) found from California to Japan; and the
black, or California, sea lion (<spn>Zalophus Californianus</spn>),
which is common on the rocks near San Francisco.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea loach</ent>⟦br⟧
